-- 
Athens Exchange Reports Record Losses in 2010, Kathimerini Says

-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 
2011-04-01T07:17:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/athens-exchange-reports-record-losses-in-2010-kathimerini-says.html
Losses at companies listed on the
 Athens Stock Exchange  in 2010 exceeded profits for the first
time,  Kathimerini  reported, citing a study by Pegasus
Securities.  The 265 companies listed on the bourse reported combined
net losses of 2.9 billion euros ($4.1 billion) in 2010 after 3.7
billion in profits in 2009, the newspaper said.  One hundred and sixty four companies reported combined
losses of 6.7 billion euros in losses in 2010 and 101 companies
reported combined profits of 3.8 billion euros, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Stoukas in  Athens  at 
 astoukas@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net . 